{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4c25d3f-a121-488b-9f14-c2a4f22a9f8c","content":"The issue is classic F# file ordering. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed **before** them in the `.fsproj`. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the compile order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019a6zgmYWkPDaoSaWKPnYwX","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-cbca2f59cfa54e01930723dcd2814aab/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-cbca2f59cfa54e01930723dcd2814aab/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"b8d2f316-508f-4df9-a1f5-86960e4e1dcd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nThe current order in the `.fsproj` is:\n1. Services.fs\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should be last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs\n2. Services.fs\n\n\n3. Program.fs","outputTokens":404,"requestId":"7C20:9309E:AAB42C:C31A55:6A02792F"},"id":"a9550f92-730c-4934-b44a-daf8f55ea46b","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:49:58.586Z","parentId":"fd5b8296-3eb7-4919-bb03-a68f3e40ad5a"}
